</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="210" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1084,1650]" pageId="6" pageNumber="210">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1589,1613]" pageId="6" pageNumber="210">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name refers to the paired slender horn-like processes of the male genitalia: Latin: cornus—a horn, gero—I carry.
</paragraph>
